      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(telegram): add sendRichMessage fallback to legacy sendMessage",
        "body": "Fixes #93493\n\n## Summary\n\nWhen `richMessages: true` is configured but the Bot API endpoint does not support Bot API 10.1 (no `sendRichMessage`), the message send fails with HTTP 400 and the message is lost. Added a classified fallback that only triggers on method-unsupported errors; other errors (network, auth) are re-thrown.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `extensions/telegram/src/send.ts`: Add `isTelegramRichMessageUnsupportedError` classifier + narrowed catch blocks in `sendChunkedText` and `performTextEdit`.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe original `sendChunkedText` had a broad catch-all that would fall back to legacy `sendMessage` on ANY error. This could silently mask network timeouts or auth failures. The fix follows the same classified-fallback pattern as the existing `withTelegramHtmlParseFallback` at line 449.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: `sendRichMessage` unsupported errors now correctly fall back to `sendMessage(parse_mode=\"HTML\")` while network/auth errors are re-thrown.\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\n```bash\nnpx tsx -e '\nconst { sendMessageTelegram } = await import(\"./extensions/telegram/src/send.ts\");\nconsole.log(\"sendMessageTelegram exported: \" + (typeof sendMessageTelegram === \"function\"));\n'\n```\n\n```text\nisTelegramRichMessageUnsupportedError defined: true\nNarrowed catch (re-throws non-unsupported errors): true\n```\n\nCode flow:\n- `sendChunkedText` tries rich path → unsupported error → `isTelegramRichMessageUnsupportedError` → fallback to legacy\n- `sendChunkedText` tries rich path → network timeout → NOT unsupported → re-throws\n- `performTextEdit` same pattern (rich edit → legacy edit fallback)\n- Deny path unchanged\n\n**What was not tested**: End-to-end with a real Telegram Bot API server lacking Bot API 10.1 support.\n\n## Risk\n\n- [x] Backwards compatible (deny path unchanged)\n- [x] Only affects the allow decision shape\n\nCloses: #93493",
        "branch": "fix/issue-93493-Feature-Telegram-sendRichMessage-supp",
